  "texts": [
    "In this study, the N obs of multiple measurements varies in the range from 3 to 31 (see Figure 3).",
    "Because the definition of STD depends on N obs, the STD results corresponding to small and large N obs values can not be compared directly.",
    "For this reason, in this work we use extent of R Hα fluctuation instead of STD to measure stellar Hα variability.",
    "For the multiple R Hα measurements of a stellar source, the extent of R Hα fluctuation (denoted by R EXT Hα) is defined as the difference between the maximum and minimum R Hα values of the source, i.e., R EXT Hα = max({R i Hα })min({R i Hα }).",
    "The value of R EXT Hα corresponds to the length of the line segments displayed in Figure 5a."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}